Jason Meyer wrote:
> So here's my question... or rather questions: This being the first time I
> have ever rotated my own tires, and tires on a very nit-picky vehicle
> nonetheless, is there a specific pattern I need to rotate the tires in?

Per Bentley, the fronts go to the back and the backs go to the front. 
It doesn't mention how the spare rotates in, but I believe you just 
rotate it in on one side and it always stays on that side (from what I 
remember reading somewhere else).
> 
> Also, once the tires are rotated, do I need to reset the air pressure for
> all the tires? It seems as if the rear tires have more air since they carry
> the brunt of the weight. With that, do I go with the air pressure suggested
> on the tires or the frame of the bus? Any recommendations on air pressure?

30 in the front, 40 in the back
